15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033813,0.055008,0.071289,0.083003,0.094223,0.10022,0.10741,0.10857,0.10452,0.095494,0.081827,0.064615],"unified_progress":[0.037689,0.063383,0.081027,0.092282,0.099133,0.10784,0.10368,0.10229,0.097383,0.091771,0.072591,0.050922]},{"section":13,"text":"Oh, maybe it's herpes zoster, which is shingles.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029898,0.059402,0.075927,0.087364,0.09482,0.099554,0.10581,0.10678,0.10191,0.095342,0.079917,0.063272],"unified_progress":[0.033381,0.063665,0.083718,0.096317,0.10118,0.10706,0.10561,0.10208,0.096293,0.090522,0.070755,0.049412]},{"section":14,"text":"Shingles can cause pain and rash along the dermatome of the affected nerve.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04252,0.060057,0.074218,0.083734,0.093144,0.097408,0.1039,0.10391,0.099455,0.090422,0.081283,0.069948],"unified_progress":[0.045134,0.070631,0.084992,0.094966,0.1002,0.1043,0.10101,0.098248,0.093974,0.08392,0.069079,0.053545]},{"section":15,"text":"The facial nerve is involved in the trigeminal area, so if the rash is in the pharynx, it might be ophthalmic or maxillary division.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032688,0.058321,0.0775,0.090813,0.099483,0.10284,0.10737,0.10372,0.099143,0.08763,0.076846,0.063646],"unified_progress":[0.034195,0.067465,0.088742,0.10088,0.10742,0.10673,0.1032,0.097207,0.097529,0.081465,0.064932,0.050233]},{"section":16,"text":"But how does that relate to the ear and taste?","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038597,0.055428,0.072416,0.082793,0.092531,0.097591,0.10126,0.10263,0.10167,0.09911,0.086046,0.069924],"unified_progress":[0.038564,0.06479,0.080534,0.091631,0.097917,0.10124,0.10118,0.099697,0.096513,0.093825,0.076613,0.0575]},{"section":17,"text":"Another thought: the ear ache and loss of taste could be due to a lesion in the geniculate ganglion, which is part of th